# Debugging and Troubleshooting Rule

Use this rule when debugging incidents, flaky tests, service failures, or production-like behavior.

## Required approach
- Reconstruct the lifecycle first: startup, readiness, steady-state, failure, shutdown.
- Check whether the bug is caused by timing, state drift, external process assumptions, or interface mismatch.
- Preserve debugging breadcrumbs in logs, tests, or comments if the failure mode is likely to recur.
- If a fix depends on an operational assumption that is not obvious in code, document it close to the logic.

## Preferred artifacts
- targeted regression tests
- improved structured logs
- comments on invariants, timing assumptions, or failure boundaries
